Umkhonto weSizwe Military Veterans Association (MKMVA) has on Wednesday pledged to assist children of former veterans to further their studies.MKMVA chairperson Kebby Maphatsoe said this at the Inaugural Golf Day held at Maccauvlei Golf Club in Vereeniging south of Johannesburg.The League was holding its first inaugural Golf day awareness in a bid to mobilise funds for the organisation. Today we are here to mark the first gold event that is meant for military veterans under the auspices of MKMVA. The purpose of this is to fundraise, we are targeting 45 military veterans coming from all the nine provinces of our country, he added.He further said the Veterans League will ensure that all funds raised in the event are used to help some of the military veterans.Today s events will be followed by an award ceremony which will be held tomorrow at Emperors Palace in Johannesburg. The league will be honouring some of the military veterans for the role they played in the country&#8217;s struggle.Among other people to be honoured for their role in transformation will be former Chief Executive Officer of Eskom Brain Molefe, SARS boss Tom Moyane and SABC Group Executive of Corporate Affairs Hlaudi Motsoeneng.Sipho Jack